An Atlantis prosecutor accused of child pornography and sexual assault has been granted bail of R1,000. CAPE TOWN - An Atlantis prosecutor appeared in court on charges of child pornography and sexual assault after he was arrested on Thursday.The prosecutor appeared nervous while standing in the dock.He has told the court he will only apply for legal representation once the investigation, which has been ongoing for three months, has been completed.The 42-year-old accused said he could not afford the R2,000 bail set by the State. Magistrate Elsa van Zyl agreed to his request for bail of R1,000.His official resignation becomes effective on Saturday.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)